nl.qiy.oic.op.qiy

Class QiyAuthorizationFlow

  • java.lang.Object
    • nl.qiy.oic.op.qiy.QiyAuthorizationFlow
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AuthorizationFlow, ServiceProviderInterface

    @Path(value="qiy")
public class QiyAuthorizationFlow
extends Object
implements AuthorizationFlow
    The authorization flow that will allow the user to log in using her Qiy Node. It starts the flow by displaying a QR code. When a callback is invoked, the flow ends.
    Since:
    12 mei 2016
    Author:
    Friso Vrolijken

      • callbackFromQiyNode

        @Path(value="callback/{random}")
 @POST
 @Consumes(value="application/json")
public static javax.ws.rs.core.Response callbackFromQiyNode(@PathParam(value="random")
                                                                                                                                            String random,
                                                                                                                                            CallbackInput cbInput)
        This method gets invoked when the user has made a connection with the node. The URL for this has been registered in startFlow(AuthenticationRequest, HttpSession) and upon connection the node invokes it. The user can now be uniquely identified, so call login
        Parameters:
        random - the random value that was used in startFlow(AuthenticationRequest, HttpSession) to register this login attempt
        cbInput - the input we said we'd like to receive
        Returns:
        Normally a 200 (OK) response to signal to the router (who made this request) that the content was received in working order
